  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A 7-year-old arhinia patient receives nasal reconstruction with nasal cavity reconstruction
      and is aided with the application of a 3D-printed nasal stent to prevent nasal cavity
      constriction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      After reconstruction of a nasal cavity in the maxilla by burring using a navigation system,
      the patient required a nasal stent to prevent stenosis. However there was no conventional
      stent available. A 3D-printed silicone nasal stent was custom made for the cavity and
      inserted.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
